 he’d be an NFT douche</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Tp6a3Cz</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/82ZynPU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Tp6a3Cz</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[qwertdeep]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Succinct answer from a US veteran</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/2oASD8K</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fpEMIkS.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://twitter.com/SAS0620/status/1496885978979610625</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/2oASD8K</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[GlobalImageServiceCat]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Favorited this maybe three years ago, had to find it for today.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/dk2JXS2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/qvX1G7Z.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/dk2JXS2</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[robertski454]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>80-year-old showed up to join the army, carrying with him a small case with 2 tshirts, a pair of extra pants, a toothbrush and a few sandwiches for lunch. He said he was doing it for his grandkids.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/LyvAc3t</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MA6Q3ub.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/LyvAc3t</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[yougotjamed]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Apparently The Ghost of Kyiv shot down 6 Russian aircraft. If true this makes them the first ace of the 21st century.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/j7xPn4H</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ozEOAiJ.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/j7xPn4H</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tonightat11DOOOOM]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Bald problems.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Dsg6QCI</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GVz5xCW.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Dsg6QCI</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SpicyNoobles]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Welp</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ivVKonX</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5scUe3f.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>No pun intended but I hope this dies in usersub. I don't want much. I'm just trying to take the first step to be able to say this out loud. 

Last November I was home alone on my day off. I took a rope that my husband bought for shibari, walked into the garage, tied it to the top of our work out rack (it is bolted into the wall so it is really sturdy), and almost went down the sewerslide. My saving grace was that I couldn't figure out how long the rope needed to be so I jumped up to do a dead hang (again, no pun intended) from the top of the rack to estimate how much I would need. 

As I was hanging by my arms the gym equipment, tools, scrap wood, law mower, and everything in the garage transformed into visions of my husband, our daughter, our son, my best friend who was getting engaged the upcoming weekend, my family and all the things I was about to say bye to. I let go of the bar and just hit the ground. I laid there for a few hours just crying and thinking of how I was about to leave my husband alone to face what I couldn't handle even as a two-person team. I thought about my children coming home from school and my curious daughter being the one to see me first. The chaos and pain I was about to unleash. The trauma I was about to make. And I was so angry that I couldn't think of all these reasons not to do it BEFORE. I got myself up. Put everything as I found it. Took a shower. And moved on. But the more I pretend nothing happened the more guilt I feel.

No need to worry about me today. I did go to the doctor and I have antidepressants that seem to be working. I'm not perfect but I'm working on it and doing better. I'm just venting here because this knowledge is a weight on my heart but I can't bring myself to say the words out loud yet. Once I can face the situation I will get some more peace. I'm just not ready. Vent here, say it out loud alone, then admit it to someone. 

Thanks for listening.

